parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility while driving, leading to accidents, especially in rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working intermittently
may start again immediately or after a few seconds or minutes
and may be accompanied by a failure of the mist switch
washer switch
or regular wiper switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of a window from the vehicle can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and may lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The side window or rear middle window falls out of the vehicle while driving
potentially due to a missing hinge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of power doors and windows can pose a risk to occupants and may lead to accidents, especially if the doors do not bounce back open when obstructed.
symptoms: Power doors fail to stay open on inclines
and power window motors may fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Wiper Performance in Inclement Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of slush and snow on wiper blades can reduce visibility while driving in cold or freezing weather, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Frozen slush is tracked across the windshield when wipers are cycled
affecting visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the frame from the insulator on the rear of the vehicle can lead to structural integrity issues, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The frame separates from the insulator on the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of exterior door handles can cause inconvenience and difficulty in entering or exiting the vehicle, potentially leading to safety issues.
symptoms: Exterior door handles fail to open
doors must be opened from the inside or through an open window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or falling interior trim and molding can cause distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Dashboard is falling off
molding around the doors is loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of power sliding doors can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the door opens while driving.
symptoms: Power sliding door opens while driving
dealer unable to locate the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Airbag and Horn Related)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the horn to malfunction, leading to a blown fuse, and in some cases, can also trigger the airbag, which can lead to a costly repair. Additionally, the electrical system failure can also cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The horn blows repeatedly
the horn blows by itself
the horn fuse blows
the airbag needs to be replaced
the electrical system fails
causing loss of power accessories
occupants are locked in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke is visible inside the vehicle
smoke is coming from the floor or dashboard
flames are visible
the vehicle is engulfed in fire
the vehicle is destroyed.
